# ============================================================================
# .cursorindexingignore — excluded from the SEARCH INDEX only.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The AI can still open and read these files when it deliberately needs to
# (e.g. checking an exact dependency version in a lockfile) — they just stop
# polluting codebase search and semantic retrieval with low-signal bulk.
#
# Rule of thumb: "noisy in search, occasionally useful on purpose" → here.
# "Never useful or never safe" → .cursorignore instead.
# ============================================================================

# --- Lockfiles (bulk noise in search; still readable for version checks) ----
package-lock.json
yarn.lock
pnpm-lock.yaml
bun.lockb
bun.lock
Cargo.lock
poetry.lock
uv.lock
Pipfile.lock
Gemfile.lock
composer.lock
go.sum
flake.lock

# --- Generated code (search should find the SOURCE, not the output) ----------
*.min.js
*.min.css
*.map
*.generated.*
*_generated.*
*.pb.go
*_pb2.py
*.g.dart
CHANGELOG.md

# --- Test snapshots & fixtures (bulk that drowns out real code in search) ----
__snapshots__/
*.snap
fixtures/
testdata/
cassettes/

# --- Vendored / third-party source kept in-repo -------------------------------
third_party/
extern/

# --- Large data files that are legitimate project content ---------------------
*.csv
*.tsv
*.ndjson
*.geojson

